If you are creating mailing labels, enter or edit the address. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/54/Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/5/54/Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/aid217882-v4-564px-Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"564","bigHeight":"423","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If you want to use a return address, select the Use return address check box, and then edit the address. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/27/Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/2/27/Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/aid217882-v4-728px-Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If you are creating another type of label, such as a book plate, type the text you want. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/0/0b/Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/0/0b/Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-400px-Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"400","bigHeight":"300","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

To print a single label, click Single label. Then, type or select the row and column number on the label sheet for the label you want to print. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/6/66/Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/6/66/Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-400px-Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"400","bigHeight":"300","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

To print the same information on a sheet of labels, click Full page of the same label. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/9/91/Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/9/91/Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-400px-Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"400","bigHeight":"300","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

To select the label type, and the type of paper feed, click Options. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/c/cc/Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/c/cc/Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-400px-Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"400","bigHeight":"300","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If the type of label you want to use is not listed in the Product number box, you might be able to use one of the listed labels, or you can click New Label to create your own custom labels. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6c/Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-3Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-3Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/6/6c/Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-3Bullet4.jpg/aid217882-v4-728px-Create-and-Print-Labels-for-a-Single-Item-or-Address-in-Microsoft-Word-Step-3Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
